newcol.steps:
\[
\begin{split}
a +_m (b +_m c) &= a +_m \overline{b + c}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step0}{= \overline{a + \overline{b + c}}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step1}{= \overline{\overline{a} + \overline{b + c}}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step2}{= \overline{a + (b + c)}}}
\end{split}
\]

collapse.steps:
\[
\begin{split}
\overline{(a + b) + c} &= \overline{\overline{(a + b)} + \overline{c}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step0}{= \overline{\overline{a + b} + {c}}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step1}{= \overline{(a +_m b) + c}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step2}{= (a +_m b) +_m c.}}
\end{split}
\]

col_li.steps:
\[
\begin{split}
a \times_m (b +_m c) &= \ol{\ol{a} \cdot \ol{b + c}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step0}{= \ol{a \cdot (b + c)}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step1}{= \ol{ab + ac}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step2}{= \ol{\ol{ab} + \ol{ac}}}}
\\&
\class{steps}{\cssId{step3}{= a\times_m b +_m a\times_m c.}}
\end{split}
\]

newcol.paragraphs:
 Let:
\[
f(x) = \begin{cases}
-x, & -1 \leq x \leq 0,\\
0, & 0 < x \leq 1.
\end{cases}
\quad,\quad
g(x) = \begin{cases}
0, & -1 \leq x \leq 0,\\
x, & 0 < x \leq 1.
\end{cases}
\]

slide.comment:
 @eg@newcol
Let $R$ be the ring of all continuous real-valued functions on $\mathbb{R}$,
then $f \in R$ is a unit if and only if it is either strictly positive or strictly negative.
@endcol@end

slide.paragraphs:
Given an integral domain $R$ (commutative, with $1 
eq 0$). We consider the set: $R 	imes R_{
eq 0} := \{(a, b) : a, b \in R, b
eq 0\}$. We define a relation $\equiv$ on $R 	imes R_{
eq 0}$ as follows: \[ (a, b) \equiv (c, d) 	ext{ if } ad = bc. \]

newcol.paragraphs:
 $\mathrm{Frac}(\mathbb{Z}) = \mathbb{Q}$,
if we identify $a/b \in \mathbb{Q}$, $a, b \in \mathbb{Z}$,
with $[(a, b)] \in \mathrm{Frac}(\mathbb{Z})$.
